# Deployment & Operations (部署与运维规范)

Scope: all DTS deployment environments

## K8s Standards

- All services deployed as K8s Deployments (stateless) or StatefulSets (stateful middleware).
- Every service must define: resource requests/limits, readiness probe, liveness probe.
- ConfigMaps for non-sensitive config. Secrets for credentials (sealed-secrets or external-secrets).
- Use PodDisruptionBudget for production workloads (minAvailable >= 1).
- Namespace: `dts-system` for platform services, `dts-packs` for AppPacks.

## Helm Chart Rules

- All services managed via Helm charts under `deploy/helm/`.
- Values hierarchy: defaults → common.yaml → environment-specific.yaml → user overrides.
- External middleware connections configurable via values (Law: default internal, support external).
- Chart version follows service version (semver).

## Image Standards

- Base images: python:3.12-slim / eclipse-temurin:21-jre / gcr.io/distroless/static (Go).
- Multi-stage builds. Final image must not contain build tools or source code.
- Image tag = git commit SHA (for traceability). Release tags additionally tagged with semver.
- All images scanned by Trivy before push. Critical CVEs block release.

## Offline Deployment

- dts-cli builds offline bundle: all images + Helm charts + CRDs + config.
- Bundle format: single tar.gz, importable via `dts-cli offline import`.
- Offline bundle must be tested in CI (air-gapped environment simulation).
- LLM for offline: Ollama/vLLM with bundled model weights (configurable model selection).

## Upgrade Strategy

- Rolling updates for stateless services (zero downtime).
- Database migrations: forward-only, backward-compatible (no destructive DDL).
- Rollback: `dts-cli rollback --to <version>` (Helm rollback + DB migration guard).
- AppPack upgrades independent of platform upgrades (version compatibility in manifest).

## Monitoring Alerts

- Every service must expose Prometheus metrics on /metrics endpoint.
- Standard alerts: pod restart loop, high error rate (>1%), high latency (P95 > SLA), disk usage > 80%.
- AI-specific alerts: accuracy drop below baseline, evaluation regression, LLM API error rate.
